FBIS3-27193 "drchi035_i_94002" FBIS-CHI-94-035 Document Type:Daily Report 22 Feb 1994 East Europe Slovak Prime Minister Arrives in Beijing 20 Feb OW2002122694 Beijing XINHUA in English 1157 GMT 20 Feb 94 OW2002122694 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Beijing, February 20 (XINHUA) -- Slovak Prime Minister Vladimir Meciar arrived here by plane today on a five-day official visit to China, at the invitation of Chinese Premier Li Peng. This is the first visit by a Slovak Government leader since the country gained independence. Meciar's entourage, numbering nearly 60 members, includes Slovak Deputy Prime Minister Sergei Kozlik, Deputy Prime Minister and Finance Minister Julius Toth, the minister of the economy, the minister of culture and some businessmen. Chairman of the Chinese Government reception committee and Vice-Minister of the Electronics Industry Lu Xinkui and Vice-Foreign Minister Dai Bingguo greeted the Slovak prime minister at the airport.
